translated:
Kjellin, Pier Gusitaif (Gösta) Vrtaliis, city physician, Lidköping, born on April 13, 1896 in Lima, Kopparberg County, son of pharmacist Gustaf Teodor Kjellin and Anna Martina Landahl. Married on September 24, 19xx to Maja Jansson. Children: Anders, born in 1924, lieutenant in the engineering troops, married in 1946 to Margit Ahlbom, Mölndal, Bror, born in 1927, student, Kerstin, born in 1929, student, Birgit, born in 1931, student. 

Education: Student exam in Uppsala in 1915, medical candidate there in 1920, medical license at the Karolinska Institute in 1925. Temporary examiner doctor in Svenljunga, Ludgo, and Heby districts for short periods in 1925, assistant doctor at AHm. Maternity ward in Stockholm the same year, temporary assistant doctor there for three months in 1926, temporary assistant doctor at Plens Clinic in 1926, assistant doctor at Mariestad Hospital from 1927-1929, including temporary chief physician for three months, assistant doctor at the epidemic hospital in Gothenburg in 1929, epidemic hospital physician and physician at the county's care home for chronically ill in Lidköping since 1929, city physician in Lidköping since 1931, first city physician there since 1946.
